Dorsal fin with oblique black blotch extending from mid-distal portion of second unbranched ray towards base of posteriormost 2 or 3 branched fin rays. Pectoral and pelvic fins with few, scattered chromatophores. Anal fin either covered by sparse chromatophores (
Fig. 2
), or with conspicuous band from middle of anterior rays to base of last rays (
Fig. 1
). Adipose fin hyaline. Caudal fin with black stripe on its lower lobe, and chromatophores more concentrated on distal portion of lower lobe.
